==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''nodus'', knot, via German ''Nudel'' (noodle).

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-noodle.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# (''usually used in the plural'') A string or strip of [[pasta]], especially as used in [[Chinese]] cookery.
# (''colloquial'') A person with poor judgement; a [[fool]].
# (''colloquial'') The [[brain]].

====Derived terms====
*[[noodle bar]]
*[[egg noodle]]

